label.value: helpers--extraction worker

definition.value: Help extraction craft workers, such as earth drillers, blasters and explosives workers, derrick operators, and mining machine operators, by performing duties requiring less skill. Duties include supplying equipment or cleaning work area.

label.value: miscellaneous extraction worker
extraction worker, all other

definition.value: All extraction workers not listed separately.

label.value: installation, maintenance, or repair occupation
supervisor of installation, maintenance, or repair worker
first-line supervisor of mechanic, installer, or repairer
first-line supervisor of mechanics, installer, or repairer

definition.value: Directly supervise and coordinate the activities of mechanics, installers, and repairers. May also advise customers on recommended services. Excludes team or work leaders.

label.value: electrical or electronic equipment mechanic, installer, or repairer
computer, automated teller, or office machine repairer (broad)
computer, automated teller, or office machine repairer

definition.value: Repair, maintain, or install computers, word processing systems, automated teller machines, and electronic office machines, such as duplicating and fax machines.

label.value: radio or telecommunications equipment installer or repairer
radio, cellular, or tower equipment installer or repairer

definition.value: Repair, install, or maintain mobile or stationary radio transmitting, broadcasting, and receiving equipment, and two-way radio communications systems used in cellular telecommunications, mobile broadband, ship-to-shore, aircraft-to-ground communications, and radio equipment in service and emergency vehicles. May test and analyze network coverage.

label.value: telecommunications equipment installer or repairer, except line installer

definition.value: Install, set up, rearrange, or remove switching, distribution, routing, and dialing equipment used in central offices or headends. Service or repair telephone, cable television, Internet, and other communications equipment on customers' property. May install communications equipment or communications wiring in buildings.

label.value: miscellaneous electrical or electronic equipment mechanic, installer, or repairer
avionics technician

definition.value: Install, inspect, test, adjust, or repair avionics equipment, such as radar, radio, navigation, and missile control systems in aircraft or space vehicles.

label.value: electric motor, power tool, or related repairer

definition.value: Repair, maintain, or install electric motors, wiring, or switches.

label.value: electrical or electronics installer or repairer, transportation equipment

definition.value: Install, adjust, or maintain mobile electronics communication equipment, including sound, sonar, security, navigation, and surveillance systems on trains, watercraft, or other mobile equipment.

label.value: electrical or electronics repairer, commercial or industrial equipment

definition.value: Repair, test, adjust, or install electronic equipment, such as industrial controls, transmitters, and antennas.

label.value: electrical or electronics repairer, powerhouse, substation, or relay

definition.value: Inspect, test, repair, or maintain electrical equipment in generating stations, substations, and in-service relays.

label.value: electronic equipment installer or repairer, motor vehicle

definition.value: Install, diagnose, or repair communications, sound, security, or navigation equipment in motor vehicles.

label.value: audiovisual equipment installer or repairer

definition.value: Install, repair, or adjust audio or television receivers, stereo systems, camcorders, video systems, or other electronic entertainment equipment in homes or other venues. May perform routine maintenance.

label.value: security or fire alarm systems installer

definition.value: Install, program, maintain, and repair security and fire alarm wiring and equipment. Ensure that work is in accordance with relevant codes.

label.value: vehicle or mobile equipment mechanic, installer, or repairer
aircraft mechanic or service technician
aircraft mechanics or service technician

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul aircraft engines and assemblies, such as hydraulic and pneumatic systems.

label.value: automotive technician or repairer
automotive body or related repairer

definition.value: Repair and refinish automotive vehicle bodies and straighten vehicle frames.

label.value: automotive glass installer or repairer

definition.value: Replace or repair broken windshields and window glass in motor vehicles.

label.value: automotive service technician or mechanic

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul automotive vehicles.

label.value: bus or truck mechanic or diesel engine specialist (broad)
bus or truck mechanic or diesel engine specialist

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul buses and trucks, or maintain and repair any type of diesel engines. Includes mechanics working primarily with automobile or marine diesel engines.

label.value: heavy vehicle or mobile equipment service technician or mechanic
farm equipment mechanic or service technician

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul farm machinery and vehicles, such as tractors, harvesters, dairy equipment, and irrigation systems.

label.value: mobile heavy equipment mechanic, except engine

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul mobile mechanical, hydraulic, and pneumatic equipment, such as cranes, bulldozers, graders, and conveyors, used in construction, logging, and mining.

label.value: rail car repairer

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul railroad rolling stock, mine cars, or mass transit rail cars.

label.value: small engine mechanic
motorboat mechanic or service technician

definition.value: Repair and adjust electrical and mechanical equipment of inboard or inboard-outboard boat engines.

label.value: motorcycle mechanic

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul motorcycles, scooters, mopeds, dirt bikes, or similar motorized vehicles.

label.value: outdoor power equipment or other small engine mechanic

definition.value: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul small engines used to power lawn mowers, chain saws, recreational sporting equipment, and related equipment.

label.value: miscellaneous vehicle or mobile equipment mechanic, installer, or repairer
bicycle repairer

definition.value: Repair and service bicycles.

label.value: recreational vehicle service technician

definition.value: Diagnose, inspect, adjust, repair, or overhaul recreational vehicles including travel trailers. May specialize in maintaining gas, electrical, hydraulic, plumbing, or chassis/towing systems as well as repairing generators, appliances, and interior components. Includes workers who perform customized van conversions.

label.value: tire repairer or changer

definition.value: Repair and replace tires.

label.value: other installation, maintenance, or repair occupation
control or valve installer or repairer
mechanical door repairer

definition.value: Install, service, or repair automatic door mechanisms and hydraulic doors. Includes garage door mechanics.

label.value: control or valve installer or repairer, except mechanical door

definition.value: Install, repair, and maintain mechanical regulating and controlling devices, such as electric meters, gas regulators, thermostats, safety and flow valves, and other mechanical governors.

label.value: heating, air conditioning, or refrigeration mechanic or installer
heating, air conditioning, or refrigeration mechanics or installer

definition.value: Install or repair heating, central air conditioning, HVAC, or refrigeration systems, including oil burners, hot-air furnaces, and heating stoves.

label.value: home appliance repairer (broad)
